        RLHF annotators decide what &ldquo;helpful&rdquo; means. If the
        annotator pool skews toward a particular demographic, political
        leaning, or cultural context, how might that affect a model&rsquo;s
        usefulness for research on politically sensitive topics?
      </p>
      <details>
        <summary>Reveal</summary>
        <div>
          <p>
            The model may systematically favour framings, perspectives, or
            conclusions that align with the annotator pool&rsquo;s views. On
            politically contested topics, it may present one position as more
            &ldquo;balanced&rdquo; or &ldquo;helpful.&rdquo; For social science
            research, this means the model is not a neutral instrument:
            its outputs carry the preferences baked in during alignment. This
            is a form of measurement bias that researchers must account for.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

