        on contested topics like immigration policy or causal
        inference methodology.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway">
      <p class="key-takeaway__label">Key Takeaway</p>
      <p>
        Post-training turns a language model into a tool.
        <strong>SFT</strong> teaches format: how to respond.
        <strong>Preference optimization</strong> (RLHF or DPO) teaches
        quality: which responses are better. <strong>Safety
        training</strong> teaches boundaries: when not to respond.
        These are design choices made by the model provider, and they shape
        every output the model produces in your research.
      </p>
    </div>

