        <div>
          <p>
            Report all three. If you only report 0.82, you are cherry-picking
            the most flattering result: the same methodological error as
            running multiple survey question versions and only reporting the one
            that confirms your hypothesis. Best practice: report the range,
            explain your selection criterion (e.g., validated against a gold
            standard), and ideally release all prompt variants with your
            replication materials.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="stop-and-think">
