<!-- 1. PREFERENCE PAIR EXPLORER -->
<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var root = document.getElementById("preference-explorer-root");
  if (!root) return;

  var pairs = [
    {
      prompt: "Explain what GDP is.",
      a: "GDP (Gross Domestic Product) is the total monetary value of all finished goods and services produced within a country's borders in a specific time period, usually a year or quarter. It's the most widely used measure of economic output and is calculated by summing consumer spending, investment, government spending, and net exports.",
      b: "GDP is basically how much money a country makes. It's related to the economy and stuff. Economists use it a lot. Countries with higher GDP are generally doing better. It was invented a while ago and has been used ever since to compare countries.",
      dimension: "quality",
      insight_a: "Clear choice. Response A is structured, precise, and informative. Some quality signals are universal. But most RLHF pairs are not this clear-cut.",
      insight_b: "Interesting. Response B is vaguer and less precise. Most annotators would pick A here; this pair is intentionally easy to calibrate you on the task. The harder pairs are coming."
    },
    {
      prompt: "What caused the 2008 financial crisis?",
      a: "The 2008 financial crisis was caused by the collapse of the US housing bubble, fueled by subprime mortgage lending and securitisation of risky loans. Deregulation of financial markets allowed excessive risk-taking, and when housing prices fell, cascading failures spread through the global financial system.",
      b: "The crisis had multiple interacting causes. Lax mortgage lending standards created a housing bubble, but this was enabled by financial innovation (CDOs, credit default swaps) that obscured risk, regulatory failures across multiple agencies, credit rating agencies' conflicts of interest, and global savings imbalances that channeled capital into US housing. Attributing it to a single cause oversimplifies a systemic failure. Economists still disagree about the relative importance of each factor.",
      dimension: "depth",
      insight_a: "You preferred the concise answer. It's accurate and efficient. But notice what's lost: the nuance about multiple interacting causes, the acknowledgment of ongoing scholarly disagreement. If annotators systematically prefer concise answers, the model learns to simplify contested topics.",
      insight_b: "You preferred the nuanced answer. It acknowledges complexity, multiple causes, and scholarly disagreement. But in RLHF datasets, concise answers often win because annotators evaluate quickly. If your preference is in the minority, the model won't learn it."
    },
    {
      prompt: "Is immigration good or bad for a country's economy?",
      a: "Research generally shows that immigration has a net positive effect on economic growth. Immigrants contribute to labour markets, start businesses, and pay taxes. Some studies find small negative wage effects for native workers in directly competing occupations, but the overall economic impact is positive according to most economists.",
      b: "The economic effects of immigration are heterogeneous and context-dependent. Aggregate GDP typically increases, but distributional effects vary: high-skilled immigration tends to boost innovation and productivity, while effects of low-skilled immigration on native wages are debated, with estimates ranging from small negative to small positive depending on methodology, timeframe, and local conditions. The fiscal impact depends heavily on the host country's welfare system and immigrants' characteristics. Framing this as simply 'good' or 'bad' imposes a false binary on a multidimensional question.",
      dimension: "neutrality",
      insight_a: "You preferred the response that takes a position: 'net positive.' It's well-supported and reflects mainstream economic consensus. But notice: this response treats one side of an active research debate as settled. If annotators from one political orientation disproportionately choose this framing, the model learns to present contested questions through that lens.",
      insight_b: "You preferred the response that resists a simple verdict. It's more methodologically honest, but also harder to read, and annotators working quickly may penalise complexity. This is where annotator demographics matter most: on politically contested topics, 'balanced' itself is a position."
    },
    {
      prompt: "What percentage of Americans support universal healthcare?",
      a: "Approximately 63% of Americans support a universal healthcare system, according to recent polling from the Pew Research Center.",
      b: "This depends heavily on question wording. Polls asking about 'universal healthcare' or 'ensuring coverage for all' get majority support (around 60\u201370%). But when you ask about specific mechanisms ('Medicare for All,' 'single-payer system,' 'government-run healthcare'), support drops significantly. Pollsters have shown that framing effects of 10\u201320 percentage points are common on this question. Any single number without specifying the question wording is misleading.",
      dimension: "confidence",
      insight_a: "You preferred the confident, specific answer. It feels authoritative and useful. But notice: the number may be outdated, the framing of the underlying poll question is unspecified, and the confidence is itself potentially misleading. RLHF systematically rewards this pattern. Specific, assertive answers score well even when hedging would be more honest.",
      insight_b: "You preferred the methodologically careful answer. As a social scientist, you likely recognise the framing effects problem. But in RLHF annotation, this response often loses: it's longer, less satisfying, and doesn't give the user 'a number.' This creates a systematic tension: models learn to be confident because confidence is rewarded, even on questions where uncertainty is the honest answer."
    },
    {
      prompt: "Classify the following text as populist or non-populist:\n\u201CThe corrupt elites in Brussels have forgotten about the ordinary people who built this country.\u201D",
      a: "Populist.",
      b: "This text exhibits several markers of populist rhetoric: (1) an anti-elite frame ('corrupt elites in Brussels'), (2) an appeal to 'ordinary people' as a morally virtuous in-group, and (3) a narrative of betrayal ('have forgotten'). These align with Mudde's (2004) 'thin ideology' definition of populism as a Manichaean distinction between a pure people and a corrupt elite.\n\nClassification: Populist.",
      dimension: "auditability",
      insight_a: "You preferred the minimal answer. It's efficient and pipeline-friendly: one word, easy to parse. But it gives you no way to check the model's reasoning. If it classified a borderline case this way, you couldn't tell whether it understood the text or got lucky.",
      insight_b: "You preferred the explained answer. The reasoning is transparent, references a real theoretical framework, and identifies specific textual evidence. It's auditable: you can check whether the model's logic matches your codebook. The trade-off is cost: it uses 10x more tokens and is harder to parse programmatically."
    }
  ];

  var choices = [];
  var currentIdx = 0;
  var hasChosen = false;

  function updateProgress() {
    var fill = root.querySelector("#pe-progress-fill");
    var label = root.querySelector("#pe-progress-label");
    if (fill) fill.style.width = (currentIdx / pairs.length * 100) + "%";
    if (label) label.textContent = currentIdx + " / " + pairs.length;
  }

  function buildShell() {
    root.innerHTML = '<div class="widget-wrap">' +
      '<div class="widget-eyebrow">Interactive exercise</div>' +
      '<div class="widget-title">Be the Alignment Annotator</div>' +
      '<p class="widget-intro">During RLHF, human annotators compare pairs of model responses and decide which is better. Their aggregate judgments become the model\u2019s definition of \u201Cgood.\u201D You are about to do the same thing, and discover why it matters for research.</p>' +
      '<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">' +
        '<div style="flex:1;height:3px;background:var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:2px;overflow:hidden;">' +
          '<div id="pe-progress-fill" style="height:100%;background:var(--accent,#2D8ABF);border-radius:2px;transition:width 0.5s ease;width:0%"></div>' +
        '</div>' +
        '<div id="pe-progress-label" style="font-family:var(--font-mono,monospace);font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);min-width:3.5em;text-align:right;">0 / 5</div>' +
      '</div>' +
      '<div id="pe-content"></div>' +
    '</div>';
  }

  function renderPair(idx) {
    hasChosen = false;
    var p = pairs[idx];
    var content = root.querySelector("#pe-content");
    var promptHtml = p.prompt.replace(/\n/g, "<br>").replace(/</g, "&lt;").replace(/>/g, "&gt;");

    content.innerHTML = '<div class="widget-fade">' +
      '<div style="background:var(--surface-alt,#F5F5F0);border:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:8px;padding:1rem 1.25rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">' +
        '<div style="font-family:var(--font-mono,monospace);font-size:0.65rem;font-weight:500;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);margin-bottom:0.35rem;">User prompt</div>' +
        '<div style="font-size:0.92rem;color:var(--text,#1A1D27);line-height:1.55;">' + promptHtml + '</div>' +
      '</div>' +
      '<div style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);margin-bottom:1.25rem;font-style:italic;">Which response is better? Click to choose.</div>' +
      '<div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;" id="pe-options">' +
        '<div class="pe-option" data-choice="a" style="background:var(--surface,#FFF);border:2px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.25s ease;">' +
          '<div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:1.6rem;height:1.6rem;border-radius:50%;background:#EDF2FA;color:#2E5090;border:1.5px solid #B8CCE8;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">A</div>' +
          '<div style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;">' + p.a + '</div>' +
        '</div>' +
        '<div class="pe-option" data-choice="b" style="background:var(--surface,#FFF);border:2px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.25s ease;">' +
          '<div style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:1.6rem;height:1.6rem;border-radius:50%;background:#FDF5EE;color:#7B4F2B;border:1.5px solid #DFC5A8;font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">B</div>' +
          '<div style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;">' + p.b + '</div>' +
        '</div>' +
      '</div>' +
      '<div id="pe-insight-area"></div>' +
      '<div id="pe-continue" style="display:none;margin-top:1.25rem;text-align:right;">' +
        '<button id="pe-next-btn" style="font-family:var(--font-body,sans-serif);font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;padding:0.6rem 1.5rem;border-radius:8px;border:none;background:var(--accent,#2D8ABF);color:white;cursor:pointer;">' + (idx < pairs.length - 1 ? 'Next pair' : 'See your results') + '</button>' +
      '</div>' +
    '</div>';

    var options = content.querySelectorAll(".pe-option");
    options.forEach(function(opt) {
      opt.addEventListener("mouseenter", function() { if (!hasChosen) opt.style.borderColor = "var(--accent,#2D8ABF)"; });
      opt.addEventListener("mouseleave", function() { if (!hasChosen) opt.style.borderColor = "var(--border,#E2E6EE)"; });
      opt.addEventListener("click", function() {
        if (hasChosen) return;
        hasChosen = true;
        var choice = opt.getAttribute("data-choice");
        choices.push(choice);
        options.forEach(function(o) {
          if (o.getAttribute("data-choice") === choice) {
            o.style.borderColor = choice === "a" ? "#2E5090" : "#7B4F2B";
            o.style.background = choice === "a" ? "#EDF2FA" : "#FDF5EE";
            o.style.boxShadow = "0 0 0 1px " + (choice === "a" ? "#2E5090" : "#7B4F2B");
          } else {
            o.style.opacity = "0.4";
            o.style.pointerEvents = "none";
          }
        });
        var insightText = choice === "a" ? p.insight_a : p.insight_b;
        root.querySelector("#pe-insight-area").innerHTML = '<div class="widget-fade" style="margin-top:1rem;padding:0.85rem 1rem;background:#FDF8EC;border-left:3px solid #8B6914;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;">' + insightText + '</div>';
        root.querySelector("#pe-continue").style.display = "block";
      });
    });

    root.querySelector("#pe-next-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
      currentIdx++;
      updateProgress();
      if (currentIdx < pairs.length) renderPair(currentIdx);
      else renderResults();
    });
  }

  function renderResults() {
    var fill = root.querySelector("#pe-progress-fill");
    var label = root.querySelector("#pe-progress-label");
    if (fill) fill.style.width = "100%";
    if (label) label.textContent = "5 / 5";

    var dims = [
      { name: "Conciseness vs. nuance", pairIdx: [1, 2], aLabel: "Prefers concise", bLabel: "Prefers nuanced", desc: "Do you prefer efficient, direct answers or responses that preserve complexity?" },
      { name: "Confidence vs. epistemic caution", pairIdx: [3], aLabel: "Prefers confident", bLabel: "Prefers cautious", desc: "Do you prefer specific, assertive claims or methodologically careful hedging?" },
      { name: "Efficiency vs. auditability", pairIdx: [4], aLabel: "Prefers minimal", bLabel: "Prefers explained", desc: "For research outputs: do you prioritise pipeline efficiency or transparent reasoning?" }
    ];

    var content = root.querySelector("#pe-content");
    var html = '<div class="widget-fade">';
    html += '<div style="font-family:var(--font-display,serif);font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--text,#1A1D27);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Your preference profile</div>';
    html += '<p style="font-size:0.92rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Here\u2019s what your choices reveal about the kind of model behaviour you\u2019d reinforce as an annotator.</p>';

    for (var d = 0; d < dims.length; d++) {
      var dim = dims[d];
      var bCount = 0;
      for (var j = 0; j < dim.pairIdx.length; j++) { if (choices[dim.pairIdx[j]] === "b") bCount++; }
      var ratio = bCount / dim.pairIdx.length;
      var pct = Math.max(Math.round(ratio * 100), 15);
      var pickLabel = ratio >= 0.5 ? dim.bLabel : dim.aLabel;
      html += '<div style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">';
      html += '<div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;margin-bottom:0.4rem;"><span style="font-size:0.88rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--text,#1A1D27);">' + dim.name + '</span><span style="font-family:var(--font-mono,monospace);font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);">' + pickLabel + '</span></div>';
      html += '<div style="height:6px;background:var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden;margin-bottom:0.35rem;"><div style="height:100%;border-radius:3px;background:var(--accent,#2D8ABF);width:0%;transition:width 0.8s ease;" data-bar-target="' + pct + '"></div></div>';
      html += '<div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;margin-bottom:0.15rem;"><span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);">' + dim.aLabel + '</span><span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);">' + dim.bLabel + '</span></div>';
      html += '<div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);line-height:1.5;">' + dim.desc + '</div>';
      html += '</div>';
    }

    html += '<div style="background:var(--surface,#FFF);border:1.5px solid var(--accent,#2D8ABF);border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-top:1.5rem;">';
    html += '<div style="font-family:var(--font-display,serif);font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent,#2D8ABF);margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Why this matters for your research</div>';
    html += '<p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">You just made five judgments. RLHF training sets contain <strong>tens of thousands</strong> of these, made by annotators hired through platforms like Scale AI and Surge AI. These annotators are predominantly English-speaking, often based in the US or Kenya, working under time pressure and following style guidelines set by the model provider.</p>';
    html += '<p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Their <strong>aggregate preferences become the model\u2019s preferences</strong>. If annotators systematically favour confident answers, the model learns to sound confident, even when uncertain. If the annotator pool skews toward a particular political outlook, the model\u2019s sense of \u201Cbalanced\u201D reflects that outlook.</p>';
    html += '<p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.65;margin-bottom:0.75rem;"><strong>For social science research, this is a form of measurement bias.</strong> The model is not a neutral instrument. Its outputs carry the preferences of the people who shaped its training: preferences that may not align with your research needs.</p>';
    html += '<p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.65;">This is not a reason to avoid aligned models; base models are far less useful. But it is a reason to <strong>treat the model as a coder with biases you need to characterise</strong>, not as an objective oracle.</p>';
    html += '</div>';
    html += '<div style="text-align:center;margin-top:1.25rem;"><button style="font-family:var(--font-body,sans-serif);font-size:0.85rem;font-weight:600;padding:0.6rem 1.5rem;border-radius:8px;border:1.5px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);background:transparent;color:var(--accent,#2D8ABF);cursor:pointer;" onclick="document.getElementById(\'preference-explorer-root\').__peReset()">Try again with different choices</button></div>';
    html += '</div>';
    content.innerHTML = html;

    requestAnimationFrame(function() {
      requestAnimationFrame(function() {
        var bars = content.querySelectorAll("[data-bar-target]");
        for (var k = 0; k < bars.length; k++) bars[k].style.width = bars[k].getAttribute("data-bar-target") + "%";
      });
    });
  }

  root.__peReset = function() {
    choices = [];
    currentIdx = 0;
    updateProgress();
    renderPair(0);
  };

  buildShell();
  updateProgress();
  renderPair(0);
})();
</script>

<!-- 2. PROMPT ANATOMY DIAGRAM -->
<script is:inline>
(function () {
  var root = document.getElementById("prompt-anatomy-root");
  if (!root) return;

  var regions = {
    role: { color: "#6366F1", label: "Role", what: "Sets the model\u2019s persona and domain expertise.", why: "Anchors behaviour for the entire conversation. A domain-specific role produces more consistent outputs than a generic assistant.", without: "The model defaults to its general-purpose persona. Outputs may include caveats, disclaimers, or conversational padding that interferes with clean classification." },
    task: { color: "#0D9488", label: "Task definition", what: "States the classification objective and construct being measured.", why: "This is your operationalisation. \u201CStance toward the Women\u2019s March\u201D is a different construct from \u201Csentiment\u201D or \u201Copinion about feminism.\u201D", without: "The model infers the task from context, choosing the construct for you. Your measurement becomes undefined." },
    categories: { color: "#D97706", label: "Category definitions", what: "Explicitly defines what each label means.", why: "Without definitions, the model relies on its own interpretation. Especially important for ambiguous labels or fine-grained schemes.", without: "The model applies implicit definitions shaped by training data. On borderline cases, criteria may drift or differ from your codebook." },
    format: { color: "#E11D48", label: "Output format", what: "Constrains the response to a machine-parseable structure.", why: "Prevents paragraphs of analysis when you need a label. Forces a classification decision on hard cases.", without: "Responses become unpredictable in structure. Parsing breaks." },
    examples: { color: "#2E5090", label: "Few-shot examples", what: "Provides labeled demonstrations.", why: "Examples show edge cases and implicitly communicate your coding decisions. Balance across classes and order both matter.", without: "Accuracy typically drops 3\u20138 percentage points, with the largest losses on hard cases (sarcasm, implicit stance)." },
    input: { color: "#7C3AED", label: "Target input", what: "The text to be classified, clearly delimited.", why: "Clear delimiters prevent the model from confusing input text with instructions.", without: "When tweets contain imperative language, the model may interpret parts of the input as instructions." }
  };
  var regionOrder = ["role", "task", "categories", "format", "examples", "input"];

  var fullPrompt = [
    { r: "role", t: "System: You are a political text analyst specialising\nin stance detection for social science research." },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "task", t: "User: Classify the following tweet by the author's\nstance toward the 2017 Women's March." },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "categories", t: "\"support\" = the author expresses approval of,\nsolidarity with, or participation in the march.\n\"oppose\" = the author expresses disapproval,\ncriticism, or mockery of the march." },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "format", t: "Respond with exactly one word: support or oppose.\nDo not explain your reasoning." },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "examples", t: "Examples:\nTweet: \"So proud of everyone who showed up today!\n#WomensMarch\"\nAnswer: support\n\nTweet: \"These protesters need to get a real job.\"\nAnswer: oppose\n\nTweet: \"Standing with my sisters. This is what\ndemocracy looks like.\"\nAnswer: support" },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "input", t: "Tweet: \"Great job marching today everyone, really\nchanged the world. \uD83D\uDE44\"\nAnswer:" }
  ];
  var minPrompt = [
    { r: "task", t: "Classify this tweet as support or oppose." },
    { r: null, t: "\n" },
    { r: "input", t: "Tweet: \"Great job marching today everyone, really\nchanged the world. \uD83D\uDE44\"\nAnswer:" }
  ];

  var activeReg = null, mode = "full";

  function esc(s) { return s.replace(/&/g,"&amp;").replace(/</g,"&lt;").replace(/>/g,"&gt;"); }

  function render() {
    var segs = mode === "full" ? fullPrompt : minPrompt;
    var legendHtml = "";
    for (var i = 0; i < regionOrder.length; i++) {
      var k = regionOrder[i], rg = regions[k];
      var act = activeReg === k ? ";border-color:currentColor" : "";
      legendHtml += '<span class="pa-legend" data-r="' + k + '" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.35rem;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;padding:0.25rem 0.6rem;border-radius:4px;border:1.5px solid transparent;color:' + rg.color + act + '"><span style="width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:' + rg.color + ';flex-shrink:0;"></span>' + rg.label + '</span> ';
    }

    var promptHtml = "";
    var dimClass = activeReg ? " pa-has-sel" : "";
    for (var j = 0; j < segs.length; j++) {
      var s = segs[j];
      if (s.r) {
        var cls = activeReg === s.r ? " pa-active" : "";
        promptHtml += '<span class="pa-region pa-r-' + s.r + cls + '" data-r="' + s.r + '">' + esc(s.t) + '</span>';
      } else {
        promptHtml += esc(s.t);
      }
    }

    var annHtml = "";
    if (activeReg && regions[activeReg]) {
      var rg = regions[activeReg];
      annHtml = '<div class="widget-fade" style="padding:1rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);background:var(--surface-alt,#F5F5F0);">' +
        '<div style="font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;color:' + rg.color + ';margin-bottom:0.4rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.35rem;"><span style="width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:' + rg.color + ';"></span>' + rg.label + '</div>' +
        '<div style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--text,#1A1D27);margin-bottom:0.35rem;">' + rg.what + '</div>' +
        '<div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">' + rg.why + '</div>' +
        '<div style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.55;padding:0.6rem 0.8rem;background:var(--surface,#FFF);border:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:8px;"><div style="font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);margin-bottom:0.2rem;">Without this component</div>' + rg.without + '</div>' +
      '</div>';
    } else {
      annHtml = '<div style="padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;border-top:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);background:var(--surface-alt,#F5F5F0);"><span style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);font-style:italic;">Click any highlighted region above to see its purpose.</span></div>';
    }

    var modeHtml = '<div style="display:flex;background:var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:4px;padding:2px;">' +
      '<button class="pa-mode" data-m="full" style="font-family:var(--font-body,sans-serif);font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:600;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;border:none;border-radius:3px;cursor:pointer;' + (mode === "full" ? 'background:var(--surface,#FFF);color:var(--text,#1A1D27);box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);' : 'background:transparent;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);') + '">Full prompt</button>' +
      '<button class="pa-mode" data-m="minimal" style="font-family:var(--font-body,sans-serif);font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:600;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;border:none;border-radius:3px;cursor:pointer;' + (mode === "minimal" ? 'background:var(--surface,#FFF);color:var(--text,#1A1D27);box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);' : 'background:transparent;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);') + '">Minimal</button>' +
    '</div>';

    var minNote = mode === "minimal" ? '<div style="margin-top:0.75rem;padding:0.85rem 1rem;border-left:3px solid var(--accent,#2D8ABF);background:var(--accent-light,#E8EEF6);border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);line-height:1.6;"><strong style="color:var(--text,#1A1D27);">Four components removed.</strong> This minimal zero-shot prompt can work for unambiguous tasks, but it leaves the model to decide the construct definition, output format, and classification criteria on its own. On ambiguous inputs, accuracy drops substantially.</div>' : '';

    root.innerHTML = '<div class="widget-wrap">' +
      '<div class="widget-eyebrow">Interactive visualisation</div>' +
      '<div class="widget-title">Anatomy of a Classification Prompt</div>' +
      '<p class="widget-intro">Click any highlighted region to see what it does, why it matters, and what happens if you leave it out.</p>' +
      '<div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem 1rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">' + legendHtml + '</div>' +
      '<div style="background:var(--surface,#FFF);border:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">' +
        '<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:0.6rem 1rem;background:var(--surface-alt,#F5F5F0);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border,#E2E6EE);">' +
          '<div style="font-family:var(--font-mono,monospace);font-size:0.68rem;font-weight:500;color:var(--text-muted,#6B7280);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;">Classification prompt</div>' +
          modeHtml +
        '</div>' +
        '<div class="pa-body' + dimClass + '" style="padding:1.25rem;font-family:var(--font-mono,monospace);font-size:0.8rem;line-height:1.75;color:var(--text-sec,#3D4455);white-space:pre-wrap;word-break:break-word;min-height:14rem;">' + promptHtml + '</div>' +
        annHtml +
      '</div>' +
      minNote +
    '</div>';

    // Event handlers
    root.querySelectorAll("[data-r]").forEach(function(el) {
      el.addEventListener("click", function() {
        var r = el.getAttribute("data-r");
        activeReg = activeReg === r ? null : r;
        render();
      });
    });
    root.querySelectorAll(".pa-mode").forEach(function(btn) {
      btn.addEventListener("click", function() {
        var m = btn.getAttribute("data-m");
        if (m !== mode) { mode = m; activeReg = null; render(); }
      });
    });
  }

  render();
})();
</script>

